Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.52,0:00:03.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnArial Black\pos(316,325)\fad(400,0)}Obey the Rules and manners\Nto have a fun Duel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.32,0:00:24.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sometime ago, for the sake of living, we left behind our happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.33,0:00:31.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We deceived ourselves, clinging to this mere illusion as we danced...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.59,0:00:37.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}With closed eyes, at the end of the horizon,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.93,0:00:43.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I was searching for your smiling face...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.35,0:00:51.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We embrace our dreams and continue on...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.36,0:00:58.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}within the swaying traces of memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.20,0:01:04.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Someday, I will once again grasp hold of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.29,0:01:12.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}these feelings I have locked away in my heart... Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.56,0:01:32.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kaiba! Sorry about your loss, pal...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.82,0:01:34.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why don't you Duel me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.40,0:01:37.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}How 'bout a battle for third place?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.20,0:01:41.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My journey on the path to become a True Duelist won't end after one measly loss!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.62,0:01:45.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Virus Combo right from the start?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.66,0:01:50.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now the only Monsters in my deck are Monsters with hardly any Attack Power!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.46,0:01:54.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But this Duel's just getting started!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.05,0:02:00.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Blue-Eyes White Dragon VS\N Blue-Eyes White Dragon"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.06,0:02:08.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Kaiba?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.98,0:02:12.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't get this far in Battle City for nothing, ya know!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.94,0:02:15.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good move, Jounouchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.78,0:02:18.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's not gonna lose, even {\i1}if{\i0} Kaiba-{\i1}kun{\i0}'s his opponent!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.15,0:02:22.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Jounouchi-{\i0}kun{\i1} has indeed grown\N much stronger as a Duelist.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.24,0:02:25.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yup! Jounouchi-{\i0}kun{\i1}'s gotten really strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.62,0:02:29.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If Malik hadn't set that Dark Game up in his Semi-Final match,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.62,0:02:31.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Jounouchi-{\i0}kun{\i1} would have won for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.43,0:02:41.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Return to me, phoenix!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.31,0:02:46.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,WHAT!?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.19,0:02:52.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}H-How...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.06,0:02:56.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Are you telling me Jounouchi's willpower\N was {\b0}stronger{\b1} than {\b0}God's attack{\b1}!?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.48,0:02:59.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My... turn...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.78,0:03:01.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Draw...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.33,0:03:06.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.54,0:03:07.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.12,0:03:12.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Gearfried... The...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.79,0:03:16.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.21,0:03:18.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A... ta...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.10,0:03:31.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If Jounouchi-{\i0}kun{\i1}'s attack had connected that moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.73,0:03:33.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}he would have beaten Malik.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.98,0:03:35.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.23,0:03:41.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When Battle City ends, I'm going to fight\N Jounouchi-{\i0}kun{\i1} just as we promised!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.03,0:03:42.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm looking forward to that moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.78,0:03:45.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yeah! It's gonna be a really good Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.87,0:03:48.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm going to defeat Malik\N for that sole purpose!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.45,0:03:49.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.04,0:03:53.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And I'm definitely going... to win!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.62,0:03:56.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I can't believe my brother's Virus Combo didn't work!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.29,0:03:59.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jounouchi's not too shabby!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.38,0:04:03.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems as though you've gained\N a fragment of wisdom on battle conduct.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.63,0:04:05.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it appears to be shallow at best.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.55,0:04:06.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.72,0:04:09.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you managed to survive this turn,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.10,0:04:16.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,your deck only contains Monsters with 1500 or lower Attack Points thanks to Deck Destruction Virus of Death!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.02,0:04:18.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You won't be getting far in this Duel relying on luck alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.03,0:04:25.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's true. I can't use my main attack force with high Attack Points like Panther Warrior or Rocket Warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.24,0:04:30.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But even so, I can't just give up\N and run away with my tail\N between my legs!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.70,0:04:32.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm going to beat you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.83,0:04:35.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And then I'm going to fulfill my promise with Yugi!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.13,0:04:38.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Go for it, Jounouchi-{\i0}kun{\i1}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.04,0:04:41.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess only death cures stupidity.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.17,0:04:47.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well! I'll give you a thorough lesson on the difference in our strength!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.05,0:04:48.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.30,0:04:48.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.43,0:04:51.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon\N Blade Knight in Attack Position!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.81,0:04:55.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attack the Swordsman of Landstar!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.64,0:04:56.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take out the garbage!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.36,0:05:06.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no! It was killed!\N Things changed in a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.61,0:05:09.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it really {\i1}was{\i0} just luck earlier?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.58,0:05:13.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No... Jounouchi-{\i0}kun{\i1} won't be taken out this easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.83,0:05:18.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll also set a reverse card face-down...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.38,0:05:20.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and end my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.67,0:05:22.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This Duel's only getting started!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.17,0:05:23.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get on with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.43,0:05:38.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What in the world\N did those two see before?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.03,0:05:49.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What in the...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.74,0:05:51.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Millennium Rod is...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.49,0:05:53.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...glowing once again!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.17,0:06:02.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What...?!\N What in the hell is happening?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.92,0:06:08.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did it only respond to {\i1}them{\i0}...?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.18,0:06:11.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm{\i0} the owner of the Millennium Rod!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.10,0:06:14.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rod! Show me what you showed them!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.03,0:06:29.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And {\i1}you{\i0} are...?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.41,0:06:34.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.58,0:06:35.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.66,0:06:40.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I come!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.04,0:06:43.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Little-Winguard in Attack Mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.30,0:06:47.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is he doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.13,0:06:51.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Won't 1400 Attack Points lose against Kaiba's Blade Knight?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.30,0:06:55.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He needs to play Defense Mode and protect his Life Points right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.93,0:06:58.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you trying to pull?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.89,0:07:02.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is the deadbeat commoner trying to think up a common strategy?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.44,0:07:03.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You could say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.11,0:07:05.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll play this thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.48,0:07:08.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Equipment Magic Card, the Legendary Sword!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.40,0:07:13.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It increases the Attack and Defense Power of the equipped Monster by 300 points!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.12,0:07:16.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good! Then it will have 1700 Attack Points!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.49,0:07:18.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be stronger than Blade Knight!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.37,0:07:21.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I equip Legendary Sword\N with little-Winguard!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.58,0:07:24.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reverse card, open!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.42,0:07:26.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Magic Absorption!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.46,0:07:27.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.84,0:07:33.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The moment your Monster's Attack Points go up,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.01,0:07:36.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,those points are absorbed by Magic Absorption and injected into my Monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.93,0:07:40.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My Legendary Sword...!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.85,0:07:46.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Use all the tricks you like.\N They won't work against me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.19,0:07:50.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're only capable of producing the strategies of a commoner! A deadbeat Duelist!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.36,0:07:54.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All you ever do is call me deadbeat and commoner over and over again!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.28,0:07:56.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set one reverse card!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.58,0:07:58.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn end!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.58,0:08:01.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It hurts me to admit it, but Kaiba-{\i1}kun{\i0} is really strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.62,0:08:04.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,True. But keep watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.79,0:08:06.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jounouchi's not giving up that easily!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.92,0:08:11.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To be more accurate, he doesn't know {\i1}how{\i0} to give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.76,0:08:14.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's your problem, little girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.64,0:08:18.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not something you can just pick up off the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.68,0:08:19.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hand it over!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.44,0:08:28.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is the Millennium Rod...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.11,0:08:30.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's {\i1}you{\i0}...!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.20,0:08:35.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.66,0:08:37.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Other me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.45,0:08:38.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This can't...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.87,0:08:41.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Millennium Puzzle is reacting to something!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.75,0:08:43.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is Malik up to something again...?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.33,0:08:47.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Anzu!!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.00,0:08:49.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You don't think he's after Anzu...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.96,0:08:53.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now that I think about it, she's been missing for a while...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.09,0:08:57.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Keep fighting, Jounouchi-{\i0}kun{\i1}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.97,0:09:04.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I thought I could win using that Equipment Magic...!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.06,0:09:07.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But Kaiba used it to power up {\b0}his{\b1} Monster
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.77,0:09:09.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now their Attack Points...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.98,0:09:12.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.07,0:09:17.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to show you such a {\i1}menacing{\i0} defeat...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.20,0:09:20.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So bad that you'll never even {\i1}think{\i0} of challenging me to a Duel again!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.87,0:09:28.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate a Magic Card! Enemy Controller!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.79,0:09:32.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card cuts my Life Points\N by 1000 points...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.25,0:09:38.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, by using the input command, I can control one of my opponent's Monsters on the field!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.93,0:09:44.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaiba-{\i1}kun{\i0} took a huge risk by lowering his Life Points by 1000!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.10,0:09:45.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is he planning to finish this in one strike?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.89,0:09:48.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Left! Right! A! B!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.52,0:09:50.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have gained control!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.74,0:09:56.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have seized Little-Winguard!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.36,0:09:58.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll then activate\N a Magic Card from my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.53,0:10:01.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cost Down activates!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.91,0:10:05.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card lowers the Monster Level of a Monster in my hand by two!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.75,0:10:07.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.62,0:10:13.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I only require one sacrifice to Summon an Eight-Star Monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.13,0:10:16.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me show you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.30,0:10:20.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is how vast the gap in our power is!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.14,0:10:24.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sacrifice Little-Winguard!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.18,0:10:28.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come forth! Blue-Eyes White Dragon!!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.50,0:10:55.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Normally I'd consider him a {\i1}waste{\i0}\N on a deadbeat like yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.92,0:10:59.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so you should be appropriately {\i1}honored{\i0}\N to be finished off by the Blue-Eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.93,0:11:01.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.22,0:11:03.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jounouchi doesn't\N have a Monster on the field!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.85,0:11:05.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Blue-Eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.68,0:11:08.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Direct Attack Jounouchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.27,0:11:10.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jounouchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.44,0:11:11.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jounouchi-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.86,0:11:14.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold your horses!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.48,0:11:16.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reverse card, open!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.11,0:11:17.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Scapegoat!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.82,0:11:18.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.45,0:11:27.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't go killing me off that soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.45,0:11:30.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God! You're really fluttering in the wind right now, Jounouchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.91,0:11:33.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a mess, but at least he made it out with his Life this turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.79,0:11:38.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You won't be damaging me until you defeat all these Scapegoats!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.21,0:11:41.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll beat them down one by one!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.34,0:11:43.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Blade Knight!!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.39,0:11:51.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! The Blade Knight's Attack Power just went up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.19,0:11:54.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's one of Blade Knight's Special Abilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.86,0:11:59.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I have one card in my hand or none at all, it gains an additional 400 Attack Points.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.15,0:12:02.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Blue-Eyes holds 3000 Attack Points.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.78,0:12:05.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the Blade Knight has 2300.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.82,0:12:10.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And {\i1}you{\i0}, who can't Summon any Monster with over 1500 Attack Points...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.41,0:12:12.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...can hope for nothing short of a miracle!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.87,0:12:18.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's true that my Scapegoats are gonna be destroyed next turn if I don't do something!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.51,0:12:20.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn end.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.92,0:12:23.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Something...! There has to be something I can do...!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.30,0:12:25.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm begging you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.93,0:12:28.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.22,0:12:30.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A let down...!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.56,0:12:33.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Can't be helped... I'll have to endure this turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.52,0:12:35.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set one reverse card!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.31,0:12:40.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I Summon Ultimator in Defense Mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.07,0:12:41.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn end!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.74,0:12:44.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a pointless struggle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.45,0:12:46.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's just see if it's pointless or not!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.03,0:12:50.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.54,0:12:54.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what you're telling me is\N you've left a piece of your memory\N within this little girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.75,0:12:59.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will no longer\N let you do as you please!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.25,0:13:00.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sure{\i0} about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.71,0:13:03.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You haven't gone\N and {\i1}forgotten{\i0}, have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.17,0:13:06.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This body belongs to {\i1}you{\i0}\N as well, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.05,0:13:07.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm aware!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.51,0:13:11.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But this is the only thing\N I can do to stop you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.56,0:13:14.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that means you're\N willing to push yourself this far?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.48,0:13:17.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you know, our dear\N elder sister's gonna be pretty {\i1}sad{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.44,0:13:21.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And {\i1}Rishid{\i0} as well...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.74,0:13:26.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you suppose he will do\N once he learns he wasn't able\N to protect you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.61,0:13:28.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Rishid...!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.37,0:13:30.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And {\i1}that's why{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.91,0:13:33.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I say you're too {\i1}soft{\i0}!!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.75,0:13:40.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the situation\N changes in a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.13,0:13:48.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You would've been better off\N if you had just stayed idly inside\N and didn't come out!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.20,0:14:11.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My oh {\i1}my{\i0},\N what an {\i1}agile{\i0} body you have!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.87,0:14:12.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still...!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.91,0:14:19.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As if a bunch of {\i1}memory fragments{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.12,0:14:21.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...could ever hope to oppose {\i1}me{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.46,0:14:25.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You're{\i0} the one who should\N disappear without a trace!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.68,0:14:31.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,VANISH!!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.76,0:14:33.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cease this at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.81,0:14:34.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.90,0:14:44.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, well... If it isn't my \N{\i1}cherished{\i0} older sister...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.86,0:14:46.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.03,0:14:48.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Malik! Hang in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.74,0:14:49.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.61,0:14:50.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm already...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.12,0:14:51.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Malik!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.87,0:14:54.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Forget about me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.20,0:14:56.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Just... defeat him...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.04,0:14:59.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Malik!!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.87,0:15:01.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the deal, elder sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.92,0:15:04.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm{\i0} the one he tried to kill here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.88,0:15:07.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heh! This isn't the least bit fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.63,0:15:09.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps I should dispose of {\i1}you{\i0} as well...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.47,0:15:16.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have no way to protect yourself\N the way you are now!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.27,0:15:16.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop this!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.48,0:15:22.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man oh {\i1}man{\i0}! I've got irritations\N up my {\i1}ass{\i0} today!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.82,0:15:28.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Malik, I'm not going to allow you\N to cause any more problems!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.28,0:15:30.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And {\i1}how{\i0} do you plan on doing that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.40,0:15:32.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Should we settle this here and now?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.63,0:15:47.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, {\i1}forget{\i0} it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.25,0:15:49.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'd be pretty {\i1}boring{\i0}\N to do things like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.88,0:15:53.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've already thought long and hard\N about the stage I'm going to kill you on.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.72,0:15:56.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll start the show in {\i1}due time{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.73,0:16:01.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait patiently while\N you've still got your {\i1}head{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.44,0:16:09.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Other me! Anzu's...!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.07,0:16:11.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anzu!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.28,0:16:13.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Anzu!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.70,0:16:14.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.70,0:16:16.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She is simply unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.58,0:16:18.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did Anzu \Ncome here in the first place?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.25,0:16:24.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yugi... I have a favor I must ask of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.88,0:16:25.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.71,0:16:27.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My little brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.84,0:16:29.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please save Malik!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.30,0:16:36.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.97,0:16:40.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Magic Card, Life-Shaving Card Treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.85,0:16:45.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Its effects allow me to draw until I have five cards in my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.15,0:16:47.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it's a Hand Reinforcement card?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.19,0:16:53.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In exchange for the hand enhancement, I must discard my entire hand after five turns.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.65,0:16:56.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I won't be needing to worry about {\i1}that{\i0} in {\i1}this{\i0} Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.78,0:16:59.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jerk! What the hell's that supposed to mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.08,0:17:02.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It means this will be over {\i1}long{\i0} before that happens!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.41,0:17:05.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Kaiser Sea Horse\N in Attack Mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.67,0:17:11.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Weaklings should go away!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.38,0:17:16.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then Blade Knight!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.56,0:17:25.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Destroy the last remaining animal, Blue-Eyes White Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.10,0:17:26.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Burst Stream of Destruction!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.90,0:17:33.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All Jounouchi's Monsters were destroyed in a matter of seconds!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.57,0:17:36.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He won't be able to block against Kaiba-{\i1}kun{\i0}'s attacks next turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.99,0:17:39.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I end my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.16,0:17:42.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And now you don't even have a wall to protect you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.54,0:17:45.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Continuing this Duel is a waste of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.12,0:17:47.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about you surrender already?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.79,0:17:50.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who the hell's gonna give in?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.71,0:17:53.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't give up in a Duel until the very last second!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.71,0:17:55.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So long as I\N have cards in my deck, anyway!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.84,0:17:58.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's called {\i1}reluctance{\i0},\N you deadbeat!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.80,0:17:59.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.93,0:18:02.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.72,0:18:05.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I've still got a chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.68,0:18:07.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Using the effects of Pot of Greed,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.60,0:18:09.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll draw twice from my deck!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.23,0:18:11.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Please! This time...!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.98,0:18:15.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! I did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.44,0:18:17.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate my reverse!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.36,0:18:18.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Graverobber!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.53,0:18:21.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaiba!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.83,0:18:24.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be taking a card\N from your Graveyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.45,0:18:25.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.45,0:18:26.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that card is...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.62,0:18:29.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Enemy Controller!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.54,0:18:36.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card lets you control the opponent's Monster by inputting a command and paying 1000 Life Points.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.84,0:18:42.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm gonna use a wee bit {\i1}different{\i0}\N command this time around.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.93,0:18:49.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Up! Left! Down! Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.31,0:18:49.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.31,0:18:53.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Using this command, I can destroy the Monster I attach the cable to!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.03,0:18:56.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You {\i1}can't{\i0}...!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.82,0:18:58.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blue-Eyes "Blows Up"!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.62,0:19:04.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And this ain't over yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.62,0:19:06.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll activate Resurrection of the Dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.41,0:19:07.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What...!?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.37,0:19:09.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the one I'll revive is, of course...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.96,0:19:12.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come out! Blue-Eyes White Dragon!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.26,0:19:19.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the ultimate combo with Graverobber and Resurrection of the Dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.97,0:19:21.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Great move, Jounouchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.93,0:19:23.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was an amazing strategy!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.47,0:19:25.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You might even {\i1}win{\i0} now!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.89,0:19:26.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.35,0:19:32.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll use Blue-Eyes\N to attack Blade Knight!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.31,0:19:34.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Burst Stream of Destruction!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.44,0:19:40.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How {\i1}dare{\i0} you...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.32,0:19:43.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I then Summon Falcon Knight\N in Defense Mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.49,0:19:45.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And this is the last one!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.95,0:19:48.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set one reverse card!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.33,0:19:50.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn end!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.54,0:19:54.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whacha think?! We don't know what's gonna happen till the very end of the Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.46,0:19:56.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why we fight 'till the end without giving up!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.96,0:20:01.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone like {\i1}you{\i0}\N dares to use my Blue-Eyes...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.34,0:20:04.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will not forgive this humiliation!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.26,0:20:07.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Blue-Eyes...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.51,0:20:12.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If Jounouchi plans to try and control you, I'll destroy you with my very own hands!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.44,0:20:15.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you go to sacrifice a Monster when Kaiser Sea Horse is in play,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.98,0:20:18.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the Monster you are about to Summon is a Light-Attribute,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.69,0:20:22.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,its Special Ability counts it as two tributes!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.74,0:20:27.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I can sacrifice two tributes for the Light-Attribute Monster, Blue-Eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.49,0:20:29.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't...! Not {\i1}another{\i0} one...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.41,0:20:32.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sacrifice Kaiser Sea Horse!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.87,0:20:36.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come forth, Blue-Eyes White Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.14,0:20:46.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you like it, deadbeat?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.14,0:20:51.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He played another Blue-Eyes?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.81,0:20:53.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They'll destroy each other!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.81,0:20:56.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Burst Stream of Destruction!!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.28,0:21:08.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn, what a guy...!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.33,0:21:13.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did he go nuts just because he didn't like the fact that I was controlling his Blue-Eyes?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.96,0:21:16.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn's not {\i1}quite{\i0} done yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.63,0:21:20.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you think you were the only one capable of reviving the dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.75,0:21:21.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.13,0:21:23.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Resurrection of the Dead...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.34,0:21:24.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Revive, my Blue-Eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.88,0:21:27.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Return to the side of your {\i1}true{\i0} master!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.27,0:21:34.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaiba also had Resurrection of the Dead in his hand?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.89,0:21:38.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's far too {\i1}disgraceful{\i0} for a fool like yourself to be using the Blue-Eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.52,0:21:41.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that Blue-Eyes is back in the hands of his {\i1}real master{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.98,0:21:44.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...you'll taste his {\i1}terror{\i0}!!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.91,0:21:53.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kaiba-{\i0}kun{\i1} managed to turn the tables as he stole back his Blue-Eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.58,0:21:55.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even though Jounouchi tries to fend him off,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.33,0:21:59.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kaiba-{\i0}kun{\i1} drives him into a pinch yet again!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.08,0:22:03.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But not giving up is one of Jounouchi's strong points!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.13,0:22:05.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Enduring several of Kaiba-{\i0}kun{\i1}'s attacks,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.63,0:22:11.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Jounouchi draws the card that has saved him in countless crises! The Time Magician!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.68,0:22:13.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Can he beat Kaiba-{\i0}kun{\i1} with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.85,0:22:14.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Next time!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.39,0:22:16.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"The Path of a True Duelist"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.23,0:22:17.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel standby!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.13,0:22:32.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The houses lined down the street drifting by being dyed red
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.49,0:22:40.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I notice pain, it'll turn into happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.06,0:22:51.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Every time people wipe away tears, they understand bonds
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.16,0:23:01.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The warm strength that you gave me will change into kindness
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.61,0:23:10.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Overflowing feelings don't stop
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.84,0:23:20.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll live while I feel it, for me to be myself
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.75,0:23:29.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Healed by overflowing friendship
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.88,0:23:34.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Our fated encounter is a truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.35,0:23:44.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and someday we'll be able to understand each other
